OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777701895
OL,3,CMet chief warns British Jews facing
OL,4,Cgreatest threat after Golders Green
OL,5,Cstabbing
OL,7,FThe Met chief and Sir Keir Starmer
OL,8,Fwere both highly critical of Green
OL,9,FParty leader Zack Polanski after he
OL,10,Fshared a social media post which
OL,11,Faccused the officers who detained the
OL,12,Fsuspect of acting "violently".
OL,14,FSir Mark told the Times: "One of the
OL,15,FTaser shots has connected but he's
OL,16,Fstill not giving up the knife. It's
OL,17,Fpretty obvious the sort of suspicion
OL,18,Fthey're going to have that he may have
OL,19,Fan explosive device."
OL,26,@tD@SOUtD@]O]vD@ZOU{D@UO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777701895
OL,3,CMet chief warns British Jews facing
OL,4,Cgreatest threat after Golders Green
OL,5,Cstabbing
OL,7,FHe said he had spoken to the officers
OL,8,Ftwo hours after the incident took
OL,9,Fplace, adding: "It's very traumatic
OL,10,Ffor them. They've got to live with
OL,11,Fthat."
OL,13,FThe Prime Minister had earlier
OL,14,Fdefended the two officers in an
OL,15,Finterview with BBC Radio 4's Today
OL,16,FProgramme.
OL,26,@qD@POUsD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30208
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1777701895
OL,3,CMet chief warns British Jews facing
OL,4,Cgreatest threat after Golders Green
OL,5,Cstabbing
OL,7,FHe told the BBC: "There's a guy on the
OL,8,Fground, he's got a rucksack on. And I
OL,9,Fdon't know what was going through the
OL,10,Fmind of those officers, but if I was
OL,11,Fthere, I'd be thinking, he's going to
OL,12,Fdetonate something. He's going to blow
OL,13,Fme up and everybody around here.
OL,15,F"In those circumstances, I think you
OL,16,Fcan quite see why what could have gone
OL,17,Fthrough their mind is, we need to do
OL,18,Fwhatever we can to disable this guy."
OL,26,@oD@ROUwD@AOUzD@eO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
